    {"topic":"Belief","difficulty":"hard","question":"The Preface Paradox arises because:","options":["Authors don't know what they've written","An author can rationally believe each claim in a book yet rationally believe (in the preface) that not all claims are true","Beliefs contradict actions","Sincerity requires certainty"],"answer":1},
