    {"topic":"Truth","difficulty":"hard","question":"The liar paradox most directly threatens:","options":["The coherence theory","Any theory that treats truth as a predicate applicable to all sentences — leading to contradictions via Tarski's undefinability theorem","Pragmatism about truth","Deflationism"],"answer":1},
