    {"topic":"Heidegger","difficulty":"medium","question":"Heidegger's concept of 'care' (Sorge) is the fundamental structure of Dasein because:","options":["Humans care about others emotionally","Care unifies the temporal structure of Dasein's existence: being-ahead-of-itself, already-in-a-world, being-amidst entities","Care is a moral virtue","It motivates all human action"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Structuralism","difficulty":"medium","question":"Post-structuralism moved beyond structuralism primarily by:","options":["Accepting fixed structures","Questioning the stability and closure of structural systems and the idea of a stable centre","Applying structuralism to more domains","Focusing on deeper universal structures"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Derrida","difficulty":"medium","question":"Derrida's critique of 'logocentrism' argues that Western philosophy has:","options":["Overvalued empirical science","Privileged speech over writing and presence over absence, treating meaning as fully present in the logos","Neglected material conditions","Ignored social context"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Husserl","difficulty":"medium","question":"The 'lifeworld' (Lebenswelt) in Husserl's late philosophy refers to:","options":["The biological world of organisms","The pre-theoretical world of everyday lived experience that underlies all scientific abstraction","The social world of culture","The economic world of production"],"answer":1},
