    {"topic":"Existentialism","difficulty":"medium","question":"Simone de Beauvoir's existentialist feminism argues that:","options":["Women's nature is biologically determined","Woman is not born but made — she is 'made' through social construction and internalized oppression","Existentialism is gender-neutral","Authentic existence is only possible for men"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Derrida","difficulty":"medium","question":"The deconstructive strategy of reversing and displacing binary oppositions involves:","options":["Eliminating both poles","First reversing the hierarchy, then showing the opposition is unstable and cannot be simply maintained","Creating new oppositions","Defending the original hierarchy"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Structuralism","difficulty":"medium","question":"Althusser's 'symptomatic reading' of Marx involves:","options":["Literal interpretation","Reading for absences and gaps — what the text cannot say but shows in its silences and problematics","Historical contextualisation","Comparing Marx to other thinkers"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Postmodernism","difficulty":"medium","question":"The postmodern critique of the 'subject' attacks:","options":["The existence of persons","The unified, autonomous, rational subject of Enlightenment philosophy as a historical and ideological construction","Political subjectivity","The concept of individual rights"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Heidegger","difficulty":"medium","question":"Heidegger's 'ready-to-hand' (Zuhanden) contrasts with 'present-at-hand' (Vorhanden) in that:","options":["Ready-to-hand entities are spatially near","Ready-to-hand is the mode of engaged, transparent tool-use; present-at-hand is the detached theoretical mode","Present-at-hand is the practical mode","They apply to different kinds of objects"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Logical Positivism","difficulty":"medium","question":"The Duhem-Quine thesis challenges logical positivism by showing:","options":["Observation is theory-neutral","Individual hypotheses face experience only in conjunction with auxiliary assumptions — falsification of a single hypothesis is impossible","All scientific statements are meaningful","Logic does not apply to science"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Sartre","difficulty":"medium","question":"Sartre's concept of 'radical freedom' holds that even in the worst situation humans:","options":["Have limited choices","Always retain the freedom to choose their attitude and response — even in captivity","Are determined by their past","Lack freedom under oppression"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Foucault","difficulty":"medium","question":"The 'panopticon' (Bentham/Foucault) is significant because:","options":["It maximizes punishment","The possibility of being watched at any time disciplines behavior without continuous surveillance","It rehabilitates prisoners","It separates prisoners efficiently"],"answer":1},
