    {"topic":"Linguistic Philosophy","difficulty":"medium","question":"Grice's theory of 'conversational implicature' explains how:","options":["Language is structurally determined","Speakers communicate more than the literal meaning of their words through cooperative maxims","Language games work","Meaning is verified by experience"],"answer":1},
    {"topic":"Derrida","difficulty":"medium","question":"Derrida's critique of Austin in 'Limited Inc' argues that Austin's theory fails to account for:","options":["Performative utterances","The essential possibility of iterability and citation — any utterance can be 'quoted', removing the speaker's presence Austin requires","Locutionary acts","The role of convention"],"answer":1},
